               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Daily Office Prayers and Litanies (fols. 3ra-18vb)
 II) Śǝrʿāta
                     qǝddāse “Ordinary of the Mass” (fols. 19ra-49rb)
 III) Anaphoras (fols.
                     49ra-135va)
 III-1) Anaphora of the Apostles (fols. 49ra-59va)
 III-2)
                     Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fols. 59va-61vb)
 III-3) Anaphora of Our
                     Lady by St Cyriacus of Behnesa (fols. 61vb-70rb)
 III-4) Anaphora of St
                     John, Son of Thunder (fols. 70rb-77vb)
 III-5) Anaphora of St Gregory
                     (“Hosanna-liturgy of St Gregory”) (fols. 77vb-80rb)
 III-6) Anaphora of St
                     Athanasius of Alexandria (fols. 80va-89rb)
 III-7) Anaphora of St Basil of
                     Caesarea (fols. 89rb-96ra)
 III-8) Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox Fathers of
                     Nicaea (fols. 96rb-102vb)
 III-9) Anaphora of St Epiphanius of Cyprus
                     (fols. 103ra-109rb)
 III-10) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fols.
                     109va-115rb)
 III-11) Second Anaphora of St Gregory (“Christmas-liturgy of
                     St Gregory”) (fols. 115va-122ra)
 III-12) Anaphora of St John Chrysostom
                     (fols. 122ra-127rb)
 III-13) Anaphora of St Dioscorus of Alexandria (fols.
                     127rb-129rb)
 III-14) Anaphora of St Cyril of Alexandria (fols.
                     129rb-135va)
 IV) Creed of the Apostles (fols. 135va-136rb). (see "Other
                     details")
 
 Additiones 1-3.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- Text IV is designated as ዘተረስአ፡ “that which was omitted” (<locus target="#135va">135va</locus>, l.4). This creed is used only in the
                        Anaphora of the Apostles, therefore its proper place is within Text
                        III-1.</note>
                     <note>- Text IV is written in smaller script than Texts I-III.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
