                        <date>Late 19th – early 20th cent.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ይ፡ ካ፡ for ይበል፡ ካህን፡</item>
                           <item>ይ፡ ዲ፡ for ይበል፡ ዲያቆን፡</item>
                           <item>ይ፡ ሕ፡ for ይበል፡ ሕዝብ፡</item>
                           <item>ቅዱስ፡ ቅ(ዱ)፡ ቅ፡ for ቅዱስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ቅዱስ፡</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ተሣ፡</abbr> for <expan>(እግዚኦ፡) ተሣሀለነ፡ </expan> (s. <locus target="#13va">13va</locus>)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the King; incipits and
                           headings of the texts; some of the musical notation signs above the
                           lines; abbreviations; the word ʾǝgäle in supplication formulas (s. fol.
                           27rb); elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals.
 On the incipit page of Texts I, II and III (fols. 3r, 19r,
                           49r), few lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
