                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1v">f. 1v</locus>
                           <desc>: Extensive unidentified note. </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> In Amharic. Crudely written in violet ink. The note contains many
                              names of clerics as well as Ethiopic numbers. The note probably
                              assigns to each of the deacons and priests mentioned their turns in
                              celebrating the Mass. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#2v">f. 2v</locus>
                           <desc>: Unidentified note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> In Amharic. Crudely written in violet ink. The note contains names
                              of priests as well as designations of their turns in celebrating the
                              Mass (?) in European numbers. The name of the fourth priest has been
                              crossed out. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#136rb">f. 136rb</locus>
                           <desc>: Unidentified note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> In Amharic. Crudely written, most of the words are poorly visible.
                              The note orobably contains information concerning a litigation (the
                              word ዋስ is clearly legible). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Crude notes written in the bottom margin: <locus target="#4r">4r</locus>, 57r, 130r.
 - Crude note written in the
                           upper margin: <locus target="#107r">107r</locus>.
 - Crude note
                           containing the name of ḥaläqa Gabra ʾIyasus: <locus target="#136v">136v</locus>..</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
